content:
Hello @everyone !

**Nomination period has begun for this year's ESSS Class Representative Elections!**

Below is a list of positions up for election for your convenience. 

**First Year Representatives (4)
Second Year Representatives (2)
Option Representatives (Biomedical, Computer, Electronics, Eng. Phys, Systems) (1 for each)
International Student Representative (1)**

If you, or a colleague are interested in running for a representative position within the Engineering Science Student Society, fill out the attached nomination form and the attached questionnaire and send it to elections@esss.ca to be approved. **You must get approval from the CRO (myself) before releasing any campaign materials. **


**Some quick rules:

1. A candidate can only be nominated for one representative position.
2. You are not permitted to nominate more than one person
3. Self nominations are permitted.
4. To be nominated as an Option Representative, you must already be declared, or are in process of being declared this semester (FA23) in that concentration.
5. You are not allowed to campaign until the official campaign period (Sept. 20 - 23)
6. You must gain approval from the CRO before releasing campaign material.
7. For any other clarifications, please do not hesitate to contact me.
**

**Nominations will be accepted until Saturday, Sept. 19, 2023 at 11:59 PM.** Nominees will be notified upon approval. Information regarding these representative positions can be found in the previous email with the subject "Representative Elections - 2023 to 2024" sent out earlier. 

For those interested in the director position mentioned in the last email, this is a reminder **that applications for the Director of Spirit position are due Sept. 19, 2023.** Please fill in this form to apply. 

https://forms.gle/FLVVS44DuwY2MiJAA

Please let me know if you have any questions! I look forward to receiving your nominations.

author: Gman#1890
content:
Hello @everyone!

I hope your first week of classes is going well!

**The Engineering Science Student Society (ESSS)** will soon be opening up elections for the following positions (# of openings in brackets):
**First Year Representatives (4)
Second Year Representatives (2)
Option Representatives {Biomedical, Computer, Electronics, Eng. Phys, Systems} (1 each)
International Student Representative (1)**

Selecting these representatives will have the following schedule:
**Nominations:** Thursday, Sept. 14 - Tuesday, Sept. 19
**Campaigning:** Wednesday, Sept. 20- Saturday, Sept. 23
**Voting:** Sunday, Sept. 24 - Wednesday, Sept. 27
**Winners Announced:** Approx. Friday, Sept. 29.

**Nomination forms will be sent on Thursday, Sept. 14, 2023 and must be submitted to elections@esss.ca by 11:59 PM on Sept. 19, 2023.**

For those who are running in the election for representatives, I have also **attached a questionnaire to fill out**. This will help voters to get to know you! **Please send the filled questionnaire back to me by 11:59 PM on Sept. 19, 2023**  so I can share it during the campaigning period.

Additionally, the Engineering Science Student Society is also seeking to fill the following director position:
**Director of Spirit (1 - 2)**

**Please note, that director positions (unlike representative positions) are fully application based** and will undergo an interview/selection process by members of the ESSS Executive team. To sign up for a director position, please fill in the linked form. Note that if you are nominated as a representative, you are not eligible to be a Director of Spirit. **Applications for the Director of Spirit position are due by 11:59 PM on Sept. 19, 2023.**

The Policy Manual of the ESSS is attached to this email. Please view Articles 6 and 7 for more information on the representative and director positions respectively. 

In the meantime, please do not hesitate to reach out if you have any questions!

All the best,
Gabriel Manansala

author: rj3421#0
content:
Hi @everyone, 

**There is only one week remaining to apply for financial awards! **

In order to be eligible for an award, you must meet the following conditions: 

1. Be enrolled in at least 9 academic units in the term the award is offered (  6 unit minimum allowed for students registered with the Centre for Accessible Learning)
2. Have a minimum CGPA of 2.0 at SFU (waived in your first term at SFU), and be in good academic standing


The **Student Affairs Unit** is currently looking for more applications for 
The **Engineering Science Student Society Award**, **which can grant a minimum of $2000**. 
Application should include a letter from the student or the ESSS discussing your involvement in and service to the engineering science student body

Other available awards include:
**Dr. William A. Gruver Engineering Science Memorial Award, one award at $1000**
**EA Dick Asher Award in the Faculty of Applied Sciences, one award at $13,400** ( Only self-identifying female students declared in the Computer Engineering option are eligible)
**Jesse Malm Award in Engineering Science, one award at $1000**

There are also specific conditions in addition to the above for each award, which you can learn about here:  https://www.sfu.ca/fas/current-student/scholarships.html under the terms of reference section.

**The application deadline is Monday, September 18th at 11:59 (PST) **

There is also the Engineering Undergraduate Student Project Award. You may contact the ESSS VP Academic at academic@esss.ca for unique deadlines and process.

**Please apply here**: https://coursys.sfu.ca/forms/apsc-fall-applied-sciences-scholarship-award-appli/  

**Any questions may be sent to fa_awards@sfu.ca. **

We look forward to reviewing your applications!
